SIMPLE: matrimony
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Matrimony
<hw>Mat"ri*mo*ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>matrimoine</ets>, through Old French, fr. L.
<ets>matrimonium</ets>, fr. <ets>mater</ets> mother. See
<er>Mother</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The union of man and woman as
husband and wife; the nuptial state; marriage; wedlock.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If either of you know any impediment, why ye may not be lawfully
joined together in <qex>matrimony</qex>, ye do now confess it.</q>
<rj><qau>Book of Com. Prayer (Eng. Ed.)</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of game at cards played by several
persons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Matrimony vine</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a
climbing thorny vine (<spn>Lycium barbarum</spn>) of the Potato
family.</cd> <rj><au>Gray.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Marriage; wedlock. See
<er>Marriage</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>matrisib</ent>⟦br⟧
